quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  50,40,"And [in part] of the night exalt Him and after prostration [i.e., prayer]."
  50,41,"And listen on the Day when the Caller{1} will call out from a place that is near -",1:[An angel who will call out Allāh's command for the Resurrection.]
  50,42,"The Day they will hear the blast [of the Horn] in truth. That is the Day of Emergence [from the graves]."
  51,34,"Marked in the presence of your Lord for the transgressors."
  51,35,"So We brought out whoever was in them [i.e., the cities] of the believers."
  51,36,"And We found not within them other than a [single] house of Muslims.{1}",1:[i.e., Lot and his family, excepting his wife.]
  52,25,"And they will approach one another, inquiring of each other."
  52,26,"They will say, "
  52,27,"So Allāh conferred favor upon us and protected us from the punishment of the Scorching Fire."
  53,19,"So have you considered al-Lāt and al-ʿUzzā?"
  53,20,"And Manāt, the third - the other one?{1}",1:[The three names given in this and the previous verse are those of well-known "goddesses" which were worshipped by the pagan Arabs before the spread of Islām.]
  53,21,"Is the male for you and for Him the female?"
  54,10,"So he invoked his Lord, "
  54,11,"Then We opened the gates of the heaven with rain pouring down"
  54,12,"And caused the earth to burst with springs, and the waters met for a matter already predestined."
  55,4,"[And] taught him eloquence."
  55,5,"The sun and the moon [move] by precise calculation,"
  55,6,"And the stars and trees prostrate.{1}",1:[They submit obediently to the laws of Allāh.  See 22:18.  An additional meaning of "najm" is vegetation of a kind without a trunk, stalk or stem.]
